Global Low Power Transformer Market Insights
Low Power Transformer Market size was valued at USD 9.8 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 14.5 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 5.2% from 2024 to 2030.

Low Power Transformer Market Overview
The global Low Power Transformer market was valued at approximately USD 6.1 billion in 2024 and is expected to grow at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 5.1% from 2024 to 2032. This growth is driven by increasing demand for energy-efficient transformers in residential, commercial, and industrial applications, as well as the rise in renewable energy installations. Low Power Transformers are crucial in reducing energy consumption and ensuring stable voltage regulation, making them a key component in modern power distribution networks.

